  "action_title": "Create ponds for great crested newts",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nThree before-and-after studies (including two replicated studies) in Germany and the UK found that naturally colonizing, captive-bred and translocated great crested newts established breeding populations at 57\u201375% of created ponds or sites. One systematic review in the UK found that there was no conclusive evidence that mitigation, which often included pond creation, resulted in self-sustaining populations.\nThree replicated, before-and-after studies in the UK found that up to 88% of created ponds were colonized by translocated or by small numbers of naturally colonizing\u00a0great crested newts. One replicated before-and-after study in the UK found that head-started great crested newts reproduced in 38% of created ponds."
}

{
